RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 6F Turf CR: 97. Claiming Purse 34000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS OR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANMER HALL stalked the pace from inside, bumped with outer rival at the five-sixteenths pole, shifted to the two path to take aim leaving the turn, headed the leader at the eighth pole, took over shortly after and drove clear. LANSDOWNE (GB) chased the top pair three deep, remained outside rivals on the turn and bumped twice with WHO'S CANDY near the five-sixteenths pole, took aim three wide into the lane, bid three deep with a furlong remaining and got outkicked by the winner. FRANKLIN ONE STAR set the pace from inside under pressure, cleared on the turn, cut the corner into the lane, clung to narrow lead at the eighth pole and yielded to the top pair. NEW YORK DREAMS (GB) chased between early in-hand, went two wide into the turn then angled over to the rail, roused past the quarter pole and kept on through the lane for a minor award. REALLY BIG NEWS stalked four deep to the stretch and flattened in the lane. WHO'S CANDY pressed the pace from outside, could not keep up on the turn and had to chase in the two path then got pinballed between foes at the five-sixteenths pole, then weakened in the stretch. BRAVESTONE broke slow, tracked widest up the backstretch, went five deep into the turn, trailed three wide into the lane and weakened. PER THE HORSE RACING INTEGRITY AND WELFARE UNIT, ANMER HALL HAS BEEN DQ'D FOR A POSITIVE TEST.

ICY BREEZE forwardly placed three deep early, bid three then four wide past the quarter pole, was turned away into the lane and got outkicked for second. SHAMBALA GIRL took back at the start, chased off the rail then between rivals at the back into the turn, spun three wide into the lane and improved position. DORINE'S WILD CAT broke slow on the inside, climbed at the back on the backstretch, raced inside a pair of rivals into the turn, saved ground to the stretch and never threatened. BIG UPDATE raced up close to the outside of the pacesetter early, chased between foes then two wide into the lane and weakened. BOGINSKAYA raced three deep at the back into the turn, trailed three wide into the drive and had little left for the stretch run.

Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Starts Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: I HAD THAT ONE TOO bumped inner rival at the start, rated in the two path outside a rival, took aim at the top pair leaving the far turn, rallied under right-handed urging and reached the front midstretch and drove clear. ANNIE'S HOPE was off slow to begin, pulled the rider to a forward position and stalked three then two wide around the clubhouse turn, bid two wide midway around the far turn, took over into the lane, cleared while lugging in to bother rival in upper stretch and got outkicked by the winner in the furlong grounds. WARRIOR LADY settled inside, went between rivals on the far turn then two wide into the lane, moved out in the drive and gained the show. CHERRY CHAOS stepped to the front and moved inside, showed the way to the second bend, challenged around the turn, relinquished the lead past the quarter pole, got forced in by ANNIE'S HOPE and steadied in upper stretch, then flattened to fourth. CHEVY GIRL stalked four then three wide around the first turn, went three wide into the second bend, came four wide into the stretch and also flattened out. BETSY IS THE CODE rated on the inside, continued along the rail through the far turn, cut he corner into the lane and weakened. ASHLEYS SANDCASTLE got bumped and crowded leaving the gate, raced two wide outside a rival at the back, chased three deep at the quarter pole and failed to menace. THE TRAINER OF CHERRY CHAOS CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST ANNIE'S HOPE IN UPPER STRETCH AND THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INVOLVING THE SAME INCIDENT. AFTER A REVIEW, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT ALTHOUGH ANNIE'S HOPE DID LUG IN AND CAUSE CHERRY CHAOS TO STEADY IN UPPER STRETCH, IT DID NOT COST CHERRY CHAOS A CHANCE AT A BETTER PLACING AND NO CHANGE WOULD BE MADE.
